Refactor login and password recovery functions
This update refactors login and password recovery methods in the LoginController.php file. The removed and added blocks of code improve the way request validation, view returns, and route middlewares are handled. This reorganization of code enhances the overall efficiency and readability of the codebase.

Fix refunded status label reference in OrderPayment.php
This commit changes the label reference for refunded orders from 'payment_status' to 'status' in the OrderPayment.php file. This adjustment is necessary for the correct display of refund status in the shop order management system, promoting accuracy and consistency within the code.

Remove trailing spaces in OrderPayment.php
This commit removes trailing spaces in the OrderPayment.php file, enhancing code readability and maintaining consistency in coding style. Trailing spaces often don't serve any function and can cause confusion, thus removal ensures clarity and neatness in the code.

Improve code readability in OrderPayment
This commit primarily focuses on enhancing code readability in OrderPayment.php. It has multiple adjustments including cleaner concatenation of strings, more straightforward status checks and translations of certain text to the Czech language to improve localization. The readability adjustments should also indirectly improve maintainability of the code.

Simplify remaining balance calculation in OrderPayment
The commit removes the logic to handle partly paid orders in OrderPayment.php. This results in a more streamlined calculation of the remaining balance, irrespective of the payment status. Thus, enhancing readability and maintainability of the code.

Remove partial payment logic from OrderPayment
The code snippet to check and display a green label for partially paid orders has been removed from the OrderPayment.php. The change simplifies the payment calculation process by excluding the scenario of partial payments, making the code less cluttered and easier to maintain.
